cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or model, please cite it as below."
title: "Merge-Corrected SFT Distillation into Qwen3.5-0.8B"
abstract: >-
  Reasoning distillation into Qwen3.5-0.8B via merge-corrected iterative SFT:
  each epoch the plain SFT checkpoint is compared against several mergekit-style
  merges back onto the instruct model (linear, ties, dare_linear, dare_ties,
  slerp, breadcrumbs, della) on GSM8K / MMLU / ARC-Challenge, and the best
  candidate seeds the next epoch — merging used as a correction against
  catastrophic forgetting.
authors:
  - family-names: Kerkouri
    given-names: Amine
repository-code: "https://github.com/kmamine/merge-corrected-sft-distillation-Qwen-Mythos-0.8B"
url: "https://huggingface.co/Amine-CV/Qwen3.5-0.8B-Mythos-Distill"
keywords:
  - model-merging
  - knowledge-distillation
  - supervised-fine-tuning
  - mergekit
  - qwen
  - lm-evaluation-harness
